<br>
1) For Enchanters I carry 4 Stacks of Tiny Daggers in my pack.(Pet Component) I also tip them with a few Jasper(which I normally keep about 6-7 Stacks of) in Exchange for Clarity(which they use for their Rune 3 Spell I believe.) A Single Peridot is good for a couple refreshers if your group is neer the enchanters group. And I also have Batwings(for Lev). (I really do suck up to Enchanters..Hehehe) <br>
<br>
2) For Druid types, the Bat wings work well also. A stack for a Sow is very fair. Having a Fire Beatle eye on you is handy too, for their Dots.(sometimes, their packs get full, and, they drop they eye that they use, and forget to replace it. Hehehe) I also have a stack or 2 of Fish scales on me at all times. Ya never know when you need to have some one cast enduring breath on you.<br>
<br>
I also make it a point to give the person a Nice Buff job, if I am the one in need. (i.e. AOF, Resolution, and Symbol.) I know that when I am asking for these things from others, tho they may enjoy helping, it does get tiresome to be bugged constantly for a service that you have. <br>
<br>
Accepting a tip is a personal preferance, and, is up to the individual. If you are doing Rezes just for the money, I frown upon that, but, to accept gifts that are fair to both you and the person recieving the rez, when the person really wants to, and, you know you can use it, do not screw yourself out of the small lump of plat that can go toward you making your character better, and, in that way, helping others. At the higher levels, the ones who offer to pay can afford it with no problems, and, it makes them feel better if you at least accept a token amount if they offer. Yes, it is Only Manna, but, When I do a Res, it is the Res itself, a S-Heal, and a full line of buffs, so they do not die again any time soon. Hehe. With my spirit Tome in hand, I have 202 wis, but, that still takes a big hunk out of my little blue bar, and, that is that much longer I have to sit and wait to be effective again. More than Manna, they have taken Time from me. Then again, Every situation is different. Last night, my friend Evolved got jumped in the Dreadlands, and died RIGHT at the Zone line into Kanor. He asked for a Rez, and, of course, did it without question. I guess thats another point, friends rezevs Strangers.<br>
<br>
